Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Circular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Production date: 131 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Nikasagoras. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0175.25.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1100)
